"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62386","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p>My rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State met with Premier Li and various Chinese companies to discuss areas of on-going cooperation within the nuclear power sector. During these discussions the UK and Chinese Governments signalled a deepening of their partnership on civil nuclear energy through the signing of a joint statement on civil nuclear power.</p><p>Alongside this, HMG have signed a Four Party Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) on Civil Nuclear Fuel Cycle Supply Chain with the INS, CNNC and CAEA to further cooperation across the civil nuclear backend fuel cycle, creating potential commercial opportunities for UK companies.</p><p>Both countries see the importance of working together on the UK's nuclear new build programme, China's own domestic civil nuclear programme and in third country markets, to maximise the billion pound opportunities this presents for both UK and Chinese companies.</p><p>Both the joint statement and Four Party MoU are published on our website at</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/multimillion-boost-to-uk-economy-as-china-and-uk-government-sign-civil-nuclear-agreement-and-sign-agreement-to-deepen-cooperation-on-climate-change" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/multimillion-boost-to-uk-economy-as-china-and-uk-government-sign-civil-nuclear-agreement-and-sign-agreement-to-deepen-cooperation-on-climate-change</a>.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-24T14:51:16.5780146Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62386/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62386/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62386/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-17","China","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what discussions he had on nuclear power with (a) his Chinese counterpart and (b) other members of the delegation of the Chinese prime minister during their visit to the UK in June; what matters were agreed; and if he will publish texts of any such agreements reached.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","200978"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62387","Scotland Office","false","2014-06-23","<p>The Government does not collate data which would allow calculation of a net benefit to the people of Scotland arising from the UK's membership of the EU. However, independent analysis published by the Centre for Economics and Business Research in March 2014 suggested that, in 2011, approximately 335,000 jobs in Scotland were associated with Scottish exports to the EU.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2014-06-23T16:28:37.7517799Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62387/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62387/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62387/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-06-17","UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what assessment he has made of the net benefit to people in Scotland of the UK's membership of the EU.","false","Biography information for Jim Sheridan","Paisley and Renfrewshire North","Jim Sheridan","201064"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62388","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-24","<p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>The number of young people being killed on our roads is far too high and we are determined to tackle this issue. It is an issue which, understandably, features prominently in the range of representations which we receive about road safety generally.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As part of our consideration of the way forward, we met the insurance industry on 27 January 2014 to discuss novice drivers and, in particular, our proposed research into the role which telematics can play in changing the behaviours and attitudes of new drivers. My officials regularly talk to the insurance industry and current discussions are aimed at encouraging participation in the research project before we can get it underway. We will publish the results of the research when they are available.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We will also publish the findings of the focus groups comprising parents, young people and employers which we undertook in order to get a better understanding of the issues from their perspective.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","200666 ; 200668","2014-06-24T15:18:10.1979421Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62388/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62388/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62388/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-17","Driving","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions his Department has had with the insurance industry on the behaviour and attitudes of novice drivers.","false","Biography information for James Duddridge","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge","200667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62389","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-24","<p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>The number of young people being killed on our roads is far too high and we are determined to tackle this issue. It is an issue which, understandably, features prominently in the range of representations which we receive about road safety generally.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As part of our consideration of the way forward, we met the insurance industry on 27 January 2014 to discuss novice drivers and, in particular, our proposed research into the role which telematics can play in changing the behaviours and attitudes of new drivers. My officials regularly talk to the insurance industry and current discussions are aimed at encouraging participation in the research project before we can get it underway. We will publish the results of the research when they are available.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We will also publish the findings of the focus groups comprising parents, young people and employers which we undertook in order to get a better understanding of the issues from their perspective.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","200666 ; 200667","2014-06-24T15:18:10.3702758Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62389/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62389/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62389/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-17","Driving","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will publish (a) details and (b) results of focus groups with parents, young people and employers about the behaviour and attitudes of novice drivers.","false","Biography information for James Duddridge","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge","200668"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62390","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-24","<p>The Department will shortly start seeking views and evidence from interested organisations, individuals and the devolved administrations on the best way to implement the new rules in Directive 2014/45/EU relating to historic vehicles. We will seek to minimise burdens while supporting road safety. Any changes need not come in to force in domestic legislation until May 2018.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-06-24T12:46:57.9886951Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62390/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62390/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62390/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-17","Motor Vehicles: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effect of the EU Roadworthiness Directive on the owners of historic vehicles in the UK.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","201102"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62392","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-24","<p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>The number of young people being killed on our roads is far too high and we are determined to tackle this issue. It is an issue which, understandably, features prominently in the range of representations which we receive about road safety generally.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As part of our consideration of the way forward, we met the insurance industry on 27 January 2014 to discuss novice drivers and, in particular, our proposed research into the role which telematics can play in changing the behaviours and attitudes of new drivers. My officials regularly talk to the insurance industry and current discussions are aimed at encouraging participation in the research project before we can get it underway. We will publish the results of the research when they are available.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We will also publish the findings of the focus groups comprising parents, young people and employers which we undertook in order to get a better understanding of the issues from their perspective.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","200667 ; 200668","2014-06-24T15:18:10.2760788Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62392/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62392/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62392/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-17","Roads: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent representations he has received about deaths of young people in traffic accidents; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for James Duddridge","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge","200666"
