"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62407","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-23","<p>The Digital Jobcentres project will modernise the Jobcentre digital infrastructure by delivering WiFi and Web Access Devices (WADs) across the Jobcentre network. From now until the end of October, we will be installing WiFi and new Web Access Devices (WADs) across the Jobcentre network.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The following 39 Jobcentres already have WiFi available for jobseekers to use:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><table><tbody><tr><td><p>London Bridge</p></td><td><p>Caerphilly</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Ashton under Lyme</p></td><td><p>Sutton</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Newport</p></td><td><p>Ebbw Vale</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Hammersmith</p></td><td><p>Altrincham</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Rusholme</p></td><td><p>Merthyr Tydfil</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Rugby</p></td><td><p>Hyde</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Poole</p></td><td><p>Tredegar</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Inverness</p></td><td><p>Stalybridge</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Newton Abbott</p></td><td><p>Wolverhampton</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wigan</p></td><td><p>Stretford</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Chester</p></td><td><p>Scarborough</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Warrington</p></td><td><p>Airdrie</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Swansea</p></td><td><p>Coventry</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oldham</p></td><td><p>Erdington</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Motherwell</p></td><td><p>Rotherham</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Harrogate</p></td><td><p>Sheffield, Cavendish Court</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Abertillery</p></td><td><p>Wakefield</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Bath</p></td><td><p>Shotton</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Bargoed</p></td><td><p>Blackwood</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Derby</p></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>By the end of October 2014, the remaining offices in the Jobcentre network will have WiFi installed and available for jobseekers to use.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-06-23T15:10:10.1279831Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62407/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62407/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62407/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-17","Jobcentres: WiFi","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, which jobcentres (a) do and (b) do not have wifi access for jobseekers to use.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mark Hendrick","201099"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62408","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-23","<p /> <p /> <p>Information regarding the amount paid in consolatory payments to claimants in Preston is not collated centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost. The amount paid in consolatory payments to GB claimants in each of the last three years is in the table.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Total paid in consolatory payments</p><p>£</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-2012</p></td><td><p>673,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-2013</p></td><td><p>700,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-2014</p></td><td><p>552,000</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Notes</p><p>1. The amounts are rounded to the nearest thousand</p><p>2. The information provided is for GB. Information regarding Northern Ireland is a matter for the Northern Ireland Office.</p><p>3. The information covers payments made by the following DWP business areas: Jobcentre Plus, Child Support Agency, Disability and Carers Service, The Pensions Service and Debt Management.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-06-23T15:12:35.8379358Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62408/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62408/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62408/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-17","Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much has been paid in consolatory payments for claimants in (a) Preston and (b) the rest of the UK in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mark Hendrick","201097"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62409","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-24","<p /> <p /> <p>The information for JSA and ESA sanctions is published at:</p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/</a></p><p> </p><p>New sanctions rules came into force for JSA and ESA from 22 October 2012 and 3 December 2012. The number of JSA sanctions applied for the new regime is the number of low, intermediate, and high level referrals where the decision was found against the claimant. Further information can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/jobseekers-allowance-overview-of-sanctions-rules" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/jobseekers-allowance-overview-of-sanctions-rules</a></p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-06-24T17:01:43.479364Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62409/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62409/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62409/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-17","Social Security Benefits: Nottinghamshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many benefit claimants in (a) Ashfield constituency and (b) Nottingham, have been sanctioned in the last (i) six and (ii) 12 months.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","201079"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62410","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-24","<p /> <p /> <p>The Department is keen that claimants are encouraged to attend their Work Capability Assessments, however any adjustments to the process which involve the means described would be subject to commercial and operational considerations. As such I am unable to commit to making this Departmental policy.</p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-06-24T16:36:34.8224633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62410/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62410/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62410/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-17","Work Capability Assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will make it his policy that reminders should be sent by text or other telephonic means informing people of the date, time and location of their upcoming work capability assessments.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mark Hendrick","201091"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62411","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-23","<p /> <p /> <p>The Department for Work and Pensions does not hold the information requested.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-06-23T15:00:55.2898016Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62411/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62411/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62411/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-17","National Employment Savings Trust Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much is paid out in tax relief each month for savers within the National Employment Savings Trust; and what the average amount paid out in tax relief has been to a scheme member in each month.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mark Hendrick","201126"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62412","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-23","<p /> <p /> <p>No data on causation of a health condition or disability are collected for disability living allowance or personal independence payment.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-06-23T14:53:40.3036627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62412/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62412/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62412/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-17","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people are claiming (a) disability living allowance and (b) personal independence payment following an adverse effect to a medical procedure.","false","Biography information for Graeme Morrice","Livingston","Graeme Morrice","200656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62413","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-24","<p /> <p /> <p>Claimants already in receipt of Disability Living Allowance will continue to receive it while their personal independence payment (PIP) claim is being assessed. Most claimants to PIP will already be receiving some element of financial support, for example through earnings or through receipt of other benefits such as employment and support allowance. No successful new claimant to PIP will lose out financially as claims will be backdated.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-06-24T16:31:33.5481171Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62413/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62413/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62413/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-17","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he is taking to ensure that personal independence payment applicants do not suffer financial hardship due to delays deciding their claims.","false","Biography information for Graeme Morrice","Livingston","Graeme Morrice","200657"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62414","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-23","<p /> <p /> <p>The information you have requested is not currently available.<strong>     </strong></p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-06-23T14:40:18.4863997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62414/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62414/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62414/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-17","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what comparative assessment he has made of the average waiting time for claimants of the personal independence payment who require a home consultation in (a) Ashfield constituency, (b) Nottinghamshire and (c) the UK.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","201022"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62415","Cabinet Office","false","2014-06-23","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-06-23T11:31:47.763",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62415/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62415/answer","PQ 201033.pdf","ONS Letter to Member","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62415/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-06-17","Remote Working","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many employed people worked from home in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","201033"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62416","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-23","<p> </p><p> </p><p>Five officials have acted as Senior Responsible Officer for the Universal Credit project since 2010.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-06-23T16:51:36.0600206Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62416/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62416/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62416/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-17","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many officials have acted as Senior Responsible Officer for the Universal Credit project since 2010.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","201073"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62417","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-06-23","<p>The First-tier Tribunal - Social Security and Child Support (SSCS), administered by HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service (HMCTS) hears appeals against Department for Work and Pensions' (DWP) decisions on a range of benefits including a person's entitlement to Employment and Support Allowance (ESA).</p><p> </p><p>Whilst a work capability assessment (WCA) can be a key factor in an ESA decision, it is not the only consideration. Appeals are brought against ESA refusals, and not WCA decisions themselves. The Tribunal does not record information on those ESA appeals in which the WCA decision is a factor, and as such HMCTS does not hold the specific information requested.</p><p> </p><p>Information on appeals against ESA decisions is published by HMCTS in Tribunal Statistics Quarterly. The most recent report for the period January to March 2014, published on 12 June 2014, can be viewed at:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/tribunal-statistics-quarterly-january-to-march-2014.</p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-06-23T16:42:33.3249894Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62417/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62417/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62417/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-06-17","Social Security Benefits: Medical Examinations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many (a) appeals and (b) successful appeals against Atos assessments in (i) Nottingham and (ii) Ashfield constituency there were in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","201074"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62418","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-23","<p /><p>It is estimated by the Organising Committee, Glasgow 2014 Ltd, that up to 30,000 employment opportunities will be created by the Commonwealth Games.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-06-23T16:49:00.137",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62418/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62418/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62418/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-17","Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of employment opportunities resulting from the Commonwealth Games; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","201060"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62419","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-23","<p /> <p /> <p>The Secretary of State for Work and Pensions has not had any recent discussions with the Secretary of State for Health on this subject.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-06-23T16:30:34.7852811Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62419/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62419/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62419/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-17","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Health on ensuring that people claiming benefits receive medical treatment that has been identified as enabling them to return to work; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","201057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62420","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-06-23","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given today by the Minister of State for the Armed Forces, the right hon. Member for Rayleigh and Wickford, to PQ 198710.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-06-23T16:08:00.3495798Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62420/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62420/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62420/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-06-17","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, with reference to the Cabinet Manual, paragraph 5.38, whether the convention that the House of Commons should have an advance opportunity to debate significant military action applies to the deployment of unmanned aerial vehicles outside Afghanistan when operated from RAF Waddington.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","201155"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62421","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-06-24","<p /> <p /> <p>We must do everything we can to support child witnesses and help them give their best possible evidence to bring offenders to justice.</p><p>The department does not hold data on the number of child victim and witnesses that use video links to give evidence (either a court building, or from a remote site).</p><p>The list below sets out the number of courthouses in each of the seven HMCTS Regions in England &amp; Wales; criminal justice is a devolved matter for Scotland and Northern Ireland. These facilities enable any victim or witness to appear by video link from a different court location to that of the trial court; it is also possible for third party users to access the court system through a secure bridge.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>HMCTS Region</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of courthouses enabled for remote video link.</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wales</p></td><td><p>22</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London</p></td><td><p>32</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South East</p></td><td><p>52</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South West</p></td><td><p>35</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Midlands</p></td><td><p>40</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North West</p></td><td><p>31</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North East</p></td><td><p>37</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>249</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Ashford","Damian Green","201138 ; 201139","2014-06-24T16:45:51.1971067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62421/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62421/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62421/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-06-17","Courts: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many remote sites are available and in use by child victims and witnesses in (a) each region of England, (b) Wales, (c) Scotland and (d) Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","201140"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62422","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-06-24","<p /> <p /> <p>As at 19 June 2014, 29 Registered Intermediaries (RIs) were available for use by child victims and witnesses in the Greater Manchester police force area that covers Bolton, 25 RIs for Lancashire, 81 RIs for England and 26 RIs for Wales. Support for vulnerable witnesses is a devolved matter in Scotland.</p><p>We recruited over 25 RIs this year, to increase the numbers of Active Registered Intermediaries to be used across the 43 police forces to help vulnerable witnesses.</p><p>Registered Intermediaries are available for work across multiple police force areas and the numbers quoted above do not reveal the total number of active RIs.</p><p>The number of child victims and witnesses involved in sexual abuse cases that have benefitted from the use of an RI in the last four years since the Witness Intermediary Scheme has been operational are provided in the table below. We do not hold data on cases before this time.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Age <br> 0 to 4</p></td><td><p>Age <br> 5 to 11</p></td><td><p>Age <br> 12 to 17</p></td><td><p><strong>Yearly <br> Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>131</p></td><td><p>152</p></td><td><p><strong>351</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>62</p></td><td><p>107</p></td><td><p>171</p></td><td><p><strong>340</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>87</p></td><td><p>173</p></td><td><p>165</p></td><td><p><strong>425</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>168</p></td><td><p>257</p></td><td><p>261</p></td><td><p><strong>686</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>TOTAL</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>385</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>668</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>749</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>1802</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The Ministry of Justice continues to monitor the number of Registered Intermediaries and is considering future recruitment plans. We are working with the CPS and police so that RIs are used to help more vulnerable witnesses to give their best evidence.</p>","Ashford","Damian Green","201143 ; 201144","2014-06-24T16:52:03.3423718Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62422/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62422/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62422/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-06-17","Children: Advocacy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many registered intermediaries are available for use by child victims and witnesses in (a) Bolton, (b) Lancashire, (c) England, (d) Scotland and (e) Wales.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","201141"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62423","Home Office","false","2014-07-17","<p> </p><p>Home Office Statistics does not collect information on sexual abuse cases <br>involving children.<br><br>While the Home Office does hold data for offences covered by the Sexual <br>Offences Act 2003 (which may cover some sexual abuse offences), we do not hold <br>data on how many cases there are. <br><br>The Department for Education collects and publishes information on the numbers <br>of children referred to and assessed by children's social services in England. <br>This includes statistics at local authority level on the number of children who <br>are subject of a child protection plan by category of abuse, including sexual <br>abuse.</p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-07-17T14:16:45.6560299Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62423/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62423/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62423/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-17","Offences against Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many sexual abuse cases involving children there have been in (a) Bolton, (b) Lancashire, (c) England, (d) Scotland and (e) Wales in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","201142"
