"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61997","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-06-23","<p>Lottery Distributors, including Arts Council England, are required to take account of directions issued under Section 26 (1) of the National Lottery etc. Act 1993. It is for the Arts Council to determine how best to do so in designing its strategic programmes.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-06-23T12:54:41.795089Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61997/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61997/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61997/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-06-16","National Lottery: Arts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, which Arts Council England strategic programmes are designed specifically to address the National Lottery directions issued in 2007.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","200884"
