"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62004","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-25","<p>I refer the hon Member to the answer I gave on 8 May 2014, (Official Report, column 277W) to the hon Member for Portsmouth South (Mr Hancock). In addition to the initiatives outlined in that answer, I would also note that the mental health of our personnel and veterans is a top priority for the Government and that is why we have committed £7.2 million to ensure there is extensive mental health support in place for those who need it.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-06-25T16:08:30.920055Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62004/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62004/answer","20140508 - Hansard extract Armed Forces Post-traumatic Stress Disorder.doc","20140508 - Hansard extract","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62004/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62004/answer/previousversion/3508","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","Veterans: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to improve care for veterans suffering  with psychological injuries after their service.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","200935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62005","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-23","<p> </p><p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 16 June 2014, (Official Report, column 364W), to the hon. Member for Plymouth, Moor View (Alison Seabeck).<br><br>Ongoing work will progressively refine this release as additional information becomes available and further analysis is conducted.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","200905","2014-06-23T15:25:03.7726297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62005/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62005/answer","Military Aircraft.doc Hansard Extract200905.doc","Hansard Extract 16 June 2014","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62005/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the deviations or exemptions from the Military Air Systems Certification Process that allowed the inaugural flight of the Rivet Joint aircraft on May 27 2014 were the final form that will be used for all operations.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62006","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-24","<p> </p><p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave him on 23 June 2014, (Official Report, column 98W).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-24T15:29:39.6709315Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62006/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62006/answer","Hansard Extract 200907.doc","Hansard Extract 23 June 2014","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62006/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what event or risk of event led to the approval of the Collision Warning Technology Demonstrator Programme for fast jet aircraft; when that event was identified; and where that event is recorded.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200907"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62007","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-23","<p> </p><p>Arrangements agreed at the UK-France Summit in January 2014 are entirely consistent with all of our obligations under international law including the Comprehensive Nuclear-Test Ban Treaty and the Treaty on the Non-Proliferation of Nuclear Weapons. I am withholding release of any assessments under the principle of legal professional privilege.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-23T15:26:02.2731025Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62007/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62007/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62007/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","Nuclear Weapons: Proliferation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment his Department has made of whether arrangements for defence nuclear co-operations which were agreed at the UK-France summit in January 2014 summit comply with the (a) Comprehensive Nuclear-Test Ban Treaty, (b) Treaty on the Non-Proliferation of Nuclear Weapons and (c) other aspects of international law; and if he will place in the Library a copy of any such assessments.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200908"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62008","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-23","<p> </p><p>High Temperature Resistant Concrete was considered as the most appropriate surface for the UK Joint Strike Fighter landing pads. AM-aluminium matting was considered but does not have the same durability for repeated use and would also result in a higher maintenance burden.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-23T15:33:36.4591452Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62008/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62008/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62008/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the value of purchasing AM-aluminium matting for landing pads for the JSF 35B.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200909"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62009","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-24","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my predecessor (Peter Luff) on 15 November 2011 (Official Report, column 743W).<br><br>The Nimrod MR4A aircraft programme was cancelled in November 2010, after only one aircraft was delivered which was subsequently grounded due to safety concerns.<br><br>Available financial information has not identified payments relating to the programme to any company after 20 October 2012.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-24T16:02:50.5705176Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62009/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62009/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62009/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","Nimrod Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the total cost was of the Nimrod MR4A programme; and what payments were made to each company involved in the programme after 20 October 2012.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200910"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62010","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-23","<p>The refurbishment of the existing hydrodynamics research facilities at the Atomic Weapons Establishment Aldermaston is planned to be completed by summer 2016.<br><br>The forecast cost of the refurbishment is £25.5 million.<br><br>The refurbished facilities will have a range of expected lifetimes, estimated at between 10 and 15 years.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-23T15:34:03.4006237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62010/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62010/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62010/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","AWE Aldermaston","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the completion date is for refurbishment of existing hydrodynamics research facilities at the Atomic Weapons Establishment Aldermaston; what the cost is of the refurbishment; and what the expected lifetime is of the new facilities.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200911"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62011","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-23","<p> </p><p>The requirement for Active Noise Reduction (ANR) headsets for personnel associated with operating F-35B onboard Queen Elizabeth Class (QEC) aircraft carriers will be tailored to individuals' noise exposure. As with all flight operatives on Aircraft Carriers,this will apply to personnel on the flight deck and not on other areas of the ship. The noise exposure will be dependent upon the operational employment of personnel, which will be defined through the ongoing development of operating procedures. The design specification of the headsets will be commensurate with the noise exposure, and in cognisance of The Control of Noise at Work Regulations, 2005. The preferred product is due to be ordered prior to the QEC entering service.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-23T15:48:25.5853747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62011/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62011/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62011/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","Aircraft Carriers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which personnel aboard Queen Elizabeth Class aircraft carriers will need to wear active noise cancellation headsets; how many such headsets will be required; and what the cost of such headsets will be.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62012","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-23","<p>The agreements with the French Government to undertake joint research described are detailed in Article 1 of the TEUTATES Treaty 2010. https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/228571/7975.pdf</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-23T15:26:58.5856208Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62012/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62012/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62012/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","France","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place in the Library copies of agreements with the French government to (a) undertake joint research at the Atomic Weapons Establishment Orion and Commissariat à l'Énergie Atomique Laser Megajoule, (b) allow use of hydrodynamics research facility at the Atomic Weapons Establishment and (c) peer review technical and scientific data underpinning nuclear warhead certification.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200912"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62013","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-23","<p>Full assessment has been made regarding the noise levels of the Joint Strike Fighter. Personnel noise exposure risk is managed in accordance with The Control of Noise at Work Regulations, 2005 and will include a combination of personal protective equipment and procedures to control daily noise exposure, normal practice for personnel operating machinery such as helicopters, tanks and other aircraft.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-23T15:38:55.8622594Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62013/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62013/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62013/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what risk assessment he has made of the safety of aircraft handlers and maintenance personnel due to the noise produced by the Joint Strike Fighter.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62014","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-23","<p>I am unable to place a copy of the business case that sought investment approval for project Teutates in the library as the document contains classified information.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-23T15:26:32.3347983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62014/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62014/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62014/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","France","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place in the Library a copy of the final investment approval for Project Teutates.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200913"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62015","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-23","<p>The adjustment from a fast jet aircraft with a heads-up display to one with a helmet mounted display cannot be quantified in hours as pilots are trained to operate the aircraft as a whole.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-23T15:30:49.1296182Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62015/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62015/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62015/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) actual and (b) simulated flight hours pilots need to adjust from a fast jet with a heads-up-display to one with only a helmet mounted display.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200916"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62016","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-23","<p> </p><p>The loudest operation to be conducted by the F-35B onboard an aircraft carrier is a Military Power take-off. The measured aircraft sound level of a Military Power take-off is approximately 145 dB at 135 degrees from the aircraft nose centre line, at a distance of 50 feet from the rear of the aircraft. The Military Power take-off is a standard operating procedure and managing exposure to noise is an integral part of normal embarked operations. This level of noise is similar to that of the Harrier, F18's, F15's and the same level as produced by an F-16.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-23T15:23:42.5054985Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62016/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62016/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62016/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the loudest decibel levels are that are produced by JSF 35B during operations aboard an aircraft carrier.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62017","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-18","<p>HMS OCEAN is completing refit and will soon put to sea. However, I am withholding precise details of HMS OCEAN's future programme as their disclosure would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-06-18T16:47:22.6255121Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62017/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62017/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62017/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","HMS Ocean","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when HMS Ocean will be declared fit to deploy; and when she will depart on Exercise Cougar 14.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200900"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62018","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-24","<p>The current net cost of removal of Nimrod MR4A material is £86,000. However, we expect the final net cost to be lower since some of the material removed from site has yet to be sold.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-24T15:34:34.6447373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62018/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62018/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62018/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","Nimrod Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the total cost of disposal of Nimrod MR4A associated material at RAF Kinloss.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200901"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62019","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-24","<p> </p><p>Projected spending on the Equipment Plan and Equipment Support Plan is detailed in the annual Defence Equipment Plan. The most recent edition was published on 12 February 2014.<br><br>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/279440/defence_equipment_plan_2013.pdf</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-24T14:29:40.609435Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62019/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62019/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62019/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the near cash projected spending on the Equipment Plan and Equipment Support Plan is for each year to 2018.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200902"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62020","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-23","<p> </p><p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 16 June 2014, (Official Report, column 364W), to the hon. Member for Plymouth, Moor View (Alison Seabeck).<br><br>Ongoing work will progressively refine this release as additional information becomes available and further analysis is conducted.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","200906","2014-06-23T15:25:03.4445138Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62020/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62020/answer","Military Aircraft.doc Hansard Extract200905.doc","Hansard Extract 16 June 2014","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62020/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what deviations or exemptions from the Military Air Systems Certifications Process were made for the Airseeker aircraft; when those deviations or exemptions were made; and who authorised each such deviation or exemption.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62021","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-23","<p>This information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost. However, normally the Ministry of Defence sells its assets with vacant possession, only leasing back properties for short periods pending relocation of the occupants.</p>","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison",,"2014-06-23T15:15:32.8342846Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62021/answer","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62021/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62021/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assets his Department has sold and leased back over the last 12 months; what the sale price was of each asset so sold; and what estimate his Department has made of the cost to the public purse of leasing back each such asset over the period of the lease.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200903"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62022","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-07","<p> </p><p>The number of precision-guided munitions dropped in Afghanistan in the period requested are shown in the table. No free fall bombs have been dropped in this time.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Aircraft Type</p></td><td><p>24 March 2011 to 16 June 2014[1]</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Fixed Wing</p></td><td><p>71</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Remotely Piloted Air Systems (RPAS)</p></td><td><p>317</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Use of force remains closely controlled and the avoidance of civilian casualties has been paramount. Professional crews carefully select the smallest warhead appropriate to the target being attacked to ensure they deliver the required effect, while minimising the risk to civilians.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>All UK forces operate in accordance with International Humanitarian Law, following the principles of distinction, humanity, proportionality and military necessity. The UK's clearly defined Rules of Engagement are formulated on this basis. The same strict Rules of Engagement that govern the use of conventional military aircraft also apply to RPAS and targets are always positively identified as legitimate military objectives. Reaper is the UK's only RPAS with the ability to deploy precision-guided weapons.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>[1] Inclusive</p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-07-07T15:40:52.3761272Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62022/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62022/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62022/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62022/answer/previousversion/5064","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) precision-guided munitions and (b) gravity bombs of each type have been dropped in Afghanistan by British (i) fixed-wing aircraft and (ii) unmanned aerial vehicles since 23 March 2011.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","200904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62023","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-01","<p>As was the case under previous administrations, details of internal meetings are not normally disclosed.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-07-01T15:41:56.3232243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62023/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62023/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62023/answer","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62023/answer/previousversion/5032","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-16","Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many meetings he has had with his Department's Chief Scientific Adviser in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Mr Liam Byrne","200785"
