"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62061","Department of Health","false","2014-06-23","<p>The following table provides details of payments made to the devolved administrations under the Pharmaceutical Price Regulation Scheme (PPRS) for the last three complete financial years.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="4"><p>PPRS payments made by the Department of Health to the devolved administrations in resource terms (£000s)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Northern Ireland</p></td><td><p>Scotland</p></td><td><p>Wales</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>3,388.4</p></td><td><p>6,218.8</p></td><td><p>3,464.7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>2,998.8</p></td><td><p>7,562.1</p></td><td><p>4,077.5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>2,852.5</p></td><td><p>6,865.2</p></td><td><p>3,827.8</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em> </em></p><p><em>Source</em>: Department of Health</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-06-23T14:59:15.3340114Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62061/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62061/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62061/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-16","Pharmaceutical Price Regulation Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what payments his Department has made to the devolved administrations as a consequence of rebates paid to it under the Pharmaceutical Price Regulation Scheme in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Sir Simon Burns","Chelmsford","Mr Simon Burns","200803"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62062","Department of Health","false","2014-06-23","<p>Through the Prime Minister's Challenge Fund, more than 7.5 million people in England will start to be offered increased access to local general practitioner (GP) services, including seven-day opening and appointments outside of office hours. The Fund is supporting over 1,110 practices covering every region as part of a pilot scheme.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The PM Challenge Fund is for one year and patients are expected to see positive changes from services from June/July onwards. An interim evaluation report is due in November this year. The full and final report is expected to be published in the early part of 2015-16. There will be a rolling programme of feedback on the pilots with case studies available from the summer onwards to help spread best practice across the country.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, the new GP contract introduced a new Enhanced Service, which includes a commitment to same day phone consultations with a professional in the GP surgery where necessary for the most at risk in the population.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-06-23T14:55:49.1378239Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62062/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62062/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62062/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-16","General Practitioners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to ensure GPs are accessible to patients.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","200858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62063","Department of Health","false","2014-06-23","<p>The UK Chief Medical Officers' (CMOs) guidelines for physical activity for adults is to be active daily, up to at least 150 minutes of moderate intensity activity a week. Children and young people should be active for at least 60 minutes and up to several hours every day of moderate to vigorous intensity physical activity. The guidelines were published in July 2011. More information can be found from UK CMOs' report on physical activity ‘Start Active, Stay Active'. A copy of the report has already been placed in the Library.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-06-23T14:59:14.6817155Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62063/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62063/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62063/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-16","Exercise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what definition his Department uses of an adequate amount of weekly physical activity.","false","Biography information for Mr Gerry Sutcliffe","Bradford South","Mr Gerry Sutcliffe","200783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62064","Department of Health","false","2014-06-19","<p>The Department does not hold information relating to the recovery of payments from National Health Service staff made redundant and subsequently re-employed by an NHS organisation.</p><p> </p><p>This information will be held locally by NHS organisations.</p><p> </p><p>The NHS is set to save £5.5 billion this Parliament and £1.5 billion each year thereafter, reducing unnecessary bureaucracy and freeing up extra resources for patient care.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-06-19T12:00:42.063652Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62064/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62064/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62064/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-16","NHS: Re-employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many redundancy payments have been recovered from NHS staff who have been made redundant and subsequently re-employed by an NHS organisation in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","200856"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62065","Department of Health","false","2014-06-19","<p>The information is not available in the format requested. The attached tables show that in April 2014, North West Ambulance Service responded to 95% of Category A immediately life threatening calls within 17 minutes and that 99% of calls were responded to within 31 minutes. The tables also provide response time information for each ambulance service trust in England since April 2011.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-06-19T15:04:18.4458922Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62065/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62065/answer","PQ200857 - Table.xlsx","Tables","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62065/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-16","Ambulance Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many times ambulance response times in (a) the North West and (b) each ambulance service trust in England have exceeded (i) 15, (ii) 20, (iii) 30 and (iv) 60 minutes since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Steve Rotheram","Liverpool, Walton","Steve Rotheram","200857"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62066","Department of Health","false","2014-06-19","<p>People with dementia receive care and support from many groups of professionals across the health and social care sector. By October 2013, 108,000 National Health Service staff had received Tier 1 training on dementia, enabling them to spot the early symptoms of dementia, know how to interact with people with dementia and ensure that patients receive the most appropriate care. The Government's refreshed Mandate to Health Education England, published on 1 May 2014, builds on this by setting an ambition for a further 250,000 NHS staff to receive Tier 1 training on dementia by March 2015, with the tools and training opportunities being made available to all staff by the end of 2018.</p><p> </p><p>The size of the adult social care workforce is 1.5 million people and research in 2010 indicated that over 40% of this workforce is involved in supporting people with dementia. Skills for Care estimate that over the past year over 100,000 social care workers have received some form of dementia awareness training through workforce development funding from local authorities and care providers.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter",,"2014-06-19T11:59:07.7941313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62066/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62066/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62066/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-16","Dementia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of how many non-clinical dementia specialist professionals are currently working across the health and care sector.","false","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","200824"
