"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62092","Home Office","false","2014-06-24","<p> </p><p>Drink driving is a summary offence, and not a notifiable offence. The Home Office only collects data on notifiable offences. <br><br>The number of defendants proceeded against at magistrates' courts and found guilty at all courts for offences relating to drink driving, in England and Wales from 2009 to 2013 can be viewed in Table 1. The same data for Suffolk can be viewed in Table 2. This data is held by the Ministry of Justice.<br><br>Data is not available below Police Force Area level, and so data for Bury St Edmunds cannot be provided.</p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-06-24T14:09:57.6533016Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62092/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62092/answer","PQ 200852- table.xls","Offences relating to drink driving ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62092/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-16","Driving under Influence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many drink-driving offences were recorded in (a) Bury St Edmunds, (b) Suffolk and (c) England and Wales in each of the last five years; and how many successful prosecutions for such offences there have been.","false","Biography information for Mr David Ruffley","Bury St Edmunds","Mr David Ruffley","200852"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62093","Home Office","false","2014-06-24","<p> </p><p>As was the case under previous administrations, details of internal meetings are not normally disclosed.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-06-24T14:03:28.6755061Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62093/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62093/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62093/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-16","Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many meetings she has had with her Department's Chief Scientific Adviser in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Mr Liam Byrne","200790"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62094","Home Office","false","2014-07-08","<p> </p><p> </p><p>he table below shows the number of straightforward passport applications <br>received within the UK which were processed within 3 weeks.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Month</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Proportion of straightforward applications processed within 3 weeks</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Dec 13</p></td><td><p>99.99%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan 14</p></td><td><p>99.99%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Feb 14</p></td><td><p>99.98%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mar 14</p></td><td><p>99.95%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr 14</p></td><td><p>99.59%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>May 14</p></td><td><p>92.26%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><br>Her Majesty's Passport Office does not hold a further breakdown of this information by <br>application type. The cost of bringing that information together would be <br>disproportionate and so it is not possible to provide the information you have <br>requested.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-07-08T14:10:55.6224732Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62094/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62094/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62094/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-16","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of (a) adult and (b) child passport renewal applications were processed within the three-week service standard in each of the last six months.","false","Biography information for Mr Bob Ainsworth","Coventry North East","Mr Bob Ainsworth","200841"
