"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62127","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-06-26","<p>As this Government has made previously clear, we will not take any steps to dispose of the mothballed HM Prison Wellingborough because it is sensible measure to retain reserve capacity. I have no immediate plans to change that status.</p><p> </p><p>My office will be in touch to arrange a meeting to further discuss this matter further.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright","200825 ; 200826","2014-06-26T11:03:33.1826018Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62127/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62127/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/62127/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-06-16","Wellingborough Prison","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what decisions he has made about the future of HMP Wellingborough.","false","Biography information for Mr Peter Bone","Wellingborough","Mr Peter Bone","200827"
