"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61864","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-18","<p>I last discussed this matter with my Scottish counterpart in May 2014.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-18T13:03:15.1116834Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61864/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61864/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61864/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-13","Opencast Mining: Ayrshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what recent discussions he has had with his counterpart in the Scottish Government regarding environmental and economic effects of the restoration of former open cast sites in East Ayrshire.","false","Biography information for Cathy Jamieson","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Cathy Jamieson","200725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61865","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-18","<p>Proposals have been put to me by Scottish Government Ministers asking Her Majesty's Government to provide a financial contribution towards the costs of restoring abandoned opencast coal mining sites in East Ayrshire and other areas of Scotland. I continue to give consideration to those proposals against the backdrop of other issues currently affecting the coal industry and of spending priorities more generally.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-18T13:03:59.2764817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61865/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61865/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61865/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-13","Opencast Mining: Ayrshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what progress he has made in providing funding to assist East Ayrshire Council with the restoration of former open-cast sites in East Ayrshire; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Cathy Jamieson","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Cathy Jamieson","200727"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61866","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p>In January 2014, the Department of Energy and Climate Change launched the UK's first Community Energy Strategy. As part of this, my rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State established a Community Energy Grid Connection Working Group to consider barriers to community energy project grid connections, including issues such as the cost of securing a connection and the impact this has on deployment. The Working Group is due to report to the Secretary of State in summer 2014 outlining its recommendations.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-24T14:47:46.2443693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61866/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61866/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61866/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-13","Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what estimate he has made of the number of community energy schemes that have not gone ahead due to the cost of securing a connection to the local grid; if he will make it his policy to (a) introduce standardised affordable grid connection charges for community energy schemes and (b) exempt community energy schemes from wider network upgrade costs; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","200681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61867","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p>Up to £120 million has been allocated to the Green Deal Home Improvement Fund in 2014-15. A decision on allocating funding for future years has yet to be taken. In the 2013 Autumn Statement, £150m was allocated in each of 15/16 and 16/17 towards energy efficiency in homes.</p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-06-24T14:48:23.3411188Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61867/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61867/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61867/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-13","Green Deal Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how much funding has been allocated to the Green Deal Home Improvement Fund for (a) 2014-15, (b) 2015-16, (c) 2016-17 and (d) all further years for which funding has been allocated.","false","Biography information for Caroline Flint","Don Valley","Caroline Flint","200682"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61868","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p>Up to £120 million has been allocated to the Green Deal Home Improvement Fund in 2014-15. DECC has not allocated specific levels of funding to (a) solid wall insulation, (b) other energy efficiency and insulation measures from his Department's approved list and (c) refunds for Green Deal assessments under the Green Deal Home Improvement Fund in (i) 2014-15, (ii) 2015-16, (iii) 2016-17 or (iv) over the lifetime of the fund.</p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-06-24T14:49:01.8277188Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61868/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61868/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61868/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-13","Green Deal Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how much funding his Department has allocated to (a) solid wall insulation, (b) other energy efficiency and insulation measures from his Department's approved list and (c) refunds for Green Deal assessments under the Green Deal Home Improvement Fund in (i) 2014-15, (ii) 2015-16, (iii) 2016-17 and (iv) over the lifetime of the fund.","false","Biography information for Caroline Flint","Don Valley","Caroline Flint","200684"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61869","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p>Up to £120 million has been allocated to the Green Deal Home Improvement Fund in 2014-15. A decision on allocating funding for future years has yet to be taken. In the 2013 Autumn Statement, £150m was allocated in each of 15/16 and 16/17 towards energy efficiency in homes.</p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-06-24T14:49:39.7743992Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61869/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61869/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61869/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-13","Green Deal Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how much funding his Department has allocated to the Green Deal Home Improvement Fund for the lifetime of the programme.","false","Biography information for Caroline Flint","Don Valley","Caroline Flint","200685"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61870","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-24","<p>The total number of homes supported under the GDHIF scheme will be dependent on a number of factors. Given these are unknown factors currently, the number of homes potentially supported could vary significantly. Up to £120m has been allocated to this scheme for 2014/15. A decision on allocating funding for future years has yet to be taken.</p><p> </p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker",,"2014-06-24T14:51:50.4847205Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61870/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61870/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61870/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-13","Green Deal Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what estimate his Department has made of the number of households that will receive cashback under the Green Deal Home Improvement Fund in (a) 2014-15, (b) 2015-16, (c) 2016-17 and (d) all further years for which funding has been allocated.","false","Biography information for Caroline Flint","Don Valley","Caroline Flint","200683"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61871","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-06-18","<p>The Foreign Secretary's Preventing Sexual Violence Initiative (PSVI) is global in reach. It aims to address impunity for crimes of conflict related sexual violence wherever these occur. We remain concerned at reports of a culture of impunity for rape and sexual violence and a lack of support for victims in Sri Lanka, as well as reports of the use of sexual violence as a means of torture in custody. We have engaged significantly with Sri Lanka on this issue. When the Foreign Secretary visited Sri Lanka in November 2013 to attend the Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting (CHOGM), he hosted an event to highlight concerns about allegations of sexual violence in Sri Lanka during and after the conflict, and urged Sri Lanka to sign up to the UN Declaration of Commitment to End Sexual Violence in Conflict. The UK is also supporting projects to ensure a zero tolerance approach to rape and sexual violence in Sri Lanka. Our presence at CHOGM also ensured that the final communiqué at the Commonwealth Heads of Government in Colombo in November 2013 contained the first ever commitment by member states to take action to prevent and respond to sexual violence.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2014-06-18T16:28:04.8995088Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61871/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61871/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61871/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-06-13","Sri Lanka","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, for what reason Sri Lanka has not been included as a priority country for the Preventing Sexual Violence Initiative.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","200735"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61872","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-06-18","<p>We remain concerned at reports of a culture of impunity for rape and sexual violence and a lack of support for victims in Sri Lanka, as well as reports of the use of sexual violence as a means of torture in custody. We are clear that rape and sexual violence whether during conflict or afterwards is unacceptable and must stop and we are committed to tackling sexual violence in conflict wherever it happens.</p><p>The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon Friend the Member for Richmond (Yorks) (Mr Hague) and I have urged Sri Lanka to sign up to the UN Declaration of Commitment to End Sexual Violence in Conflict, and we are supporting projects to ensure a zero tolerance approach to rape and sexual violence in Sri Lanka. On 27 March, the UN Human Rights Council agreed a resolution on Sri Lanka that establishes an international investigation into allegations of violations of international law of both sides of the military conflict, and calls upon the Sri Lankan government to make progress on reconciliation and human rights. The resolution also expresses serious concern at continuing reports of sexual and gender based violence.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2014-06-18T16:31:52.6459825Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61872/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61872/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/61872/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-06-13","Sri Lanka","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make an assessment of prevalence of sexual violence in conflict in Sri Lanka.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","200736"
